            <div id="dsq-comment-message-236245" class="dsq-comment-message"><p>There&#8217;s a woman named Ellen Brown who touts an economic theory similar to the one you seem to be espousing. She incorrectly believes that money = debt (it doesn&#8217;t), that debt is paid for by borrowing more debt (it isn&#8217;t), and that limited currencies possess some fundamental attribute or capability that make them superior to fiat currencies (they don&#8217;t).</p>
